FIRE bugs have targeted an old people's home twice in three days sparking fear among vulnerable residents.
Suspects tried to set fire to the door and window of two properties belonging to female residents at Saunders Court in Kirkcaldy.
The fires come amid a series of anti-social incidents in recent weeks.
Police are now appealing for any information regarding these incidents. Officers have been conducting high visibility patrols in the area in order to provide community reassurance.
Police Constable Mike Daglish said: “Fortunately these fires have not taken hold and burnt out quickly, however they have caused much distress to the elderly residents who have been targeted.
“We are appealing for any information regarding these incidents. Anyone who has any information is asked to contact police immediately.&quot;
